question:
Given two strings A and B&#xA0;of lowercase letters, return true if and only if we&#xA0;can swap two letters in A so that the result equals B.

&#xA0;

Example 1:


Input: A = &quot;ab&quot;, B = &quot;ba&quot;
Output: true



Example 2:

Input: A = &quot;ab&quot;, B = &quot;ab&quot;
Output: false



Example 3:

Input: A = &quot;aa&quot;, B = &quot;aa&quot;
Output: true



Example 4:

Input: A = &quot;aaaaaaabc&quot;, B = &quot;aaaaaaacb&quot;
Output: true



Example 5:

Input: A = &quot;&quot;, B = &quot;aa&quot;
Output: false


&#xA0;

Note:


	0 &lt;= A.length &lt;= 20000
	0 &lt;= B.length &lt;= 20000
	A and&#xA0;B consist only of lowercase letters.
